<TEXT>
bert lance has no official role at the democratic 
convention but jesse jackson will make sure there is a place at 
the table for the burly georgia politician declared persona non 
grata four years ago 
hes one of jesses kitchen cabinet said longtime jackson 
adviser frank watkins watkins said lances public support of 
jackson helped give the democratic presidential runnerup to 
michael dukakis tremendous credibility among democratic 
established officials and southerners in particular 
lance talks as often as four times a day to jackson watkins 
said and his advice is sometimes accepted sometimes not but 
always candid and frank and extremely helpful to the 
candidate 
beyond that lance and jackson have a close personal 
relationship that has been nurtured over the past four years of 
political hills and valleys for both men 
its a brother relationship lance said in an interview 
its not so much a political relationship as it is a real 
friendship were really close in the sense that we can joke 
with each other and be very frank with each other 
the alliance between the unlikely pair one a fiery black 
preacher and civil rights activist the other the epitome of a 
white southern insider helped lance make something of a political 
comeback from troubles that began when he was director of the 
office of management and budget under president carter 
he got rehabilitated politically and theres nothing wrong 
with that said watkins 
lance left the carter administration under a cloud of alleged 
past banking irregularities then was acquitted of those charges by 
a federal jury but he was dogged by a negative image that 
resurfaced at the democratic national convention in 1984 
walter mondale thankful for lances help in the south courted 
him during the convention to head up the democratic party then in 
the face of party protest summarily dumped him all within a matter 
of illtimed days lance ultimately stepped down as chairman of 
both mondales 1984 campaign and of the georgia democratic party 
but today its a different story lance is sought out by those 
looking for an inside track on the candidate who will walk into the 
atlanta convention with some 1200 delegates in his pocket 
in rare appearances on the campaign trail lance invariably was 
buttonholed by reporters eager for his insight 
he gamely sang jacksons praises on tv news programs giving 
early assurances that jackson was not a disruptive force but a 
loyal democrat 
and when jacksons campaign needed a public display of 
establishment acceptability as his campaign was catching fire it 
was largely through lances efforts that a meeting with democratic 
leaders was arranged in washington 
their friendship goes back to 1983 when jackson began his 
presidential bid lance had already proven himself by organizing 
southern state chairmen to go to jacksons home base of chicago and 
campaign for harold washington who became the citys first black 
mayor in a bitter election against jane byrne 
it was lance whom mondale turned to as a liaison to jackson in 
trying to deal with jacksons various complaints about party 
workings 
robert beckel who ran mondales 1984 campaign recalls an early 
negotiating meeting with lance and jackson 
it was a chemistry that worked right away they talk a lot of 
grits and gravy with each other they talk south with a natural 
affinity since jackson is from south carolina beckel said the 
two of them sit there and theyll go face to face and disagree with 
each other ive never seen two guys fight through smiling the way 
those two guys do 
tennessee politician john j hooker said their affinity stems in 
part from rejection at the hands of their own party 
their relationship was born in pain here were two men who had 
walked on the hot coals and felt that they had not been dealt with 
fairly theres no question in my mind that jesse jackson is a 
hero of bert lance and bert lance is a hero of jesse jackson 
said hooker 
</TEXT>
